               <p>JAMES HOPE. I am a broker. On the 22d or 23d of July the male prisoner offered me a bed for sale; he said he wanted to take some things out of pawn, as he was going into the country, and had lost his wife - having a hatband on, I thought it true, and bought it for 15s.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner WILLIAM FOWLE. I hope you will consider that it was by my order my wife did it.</p>
